programme.title: Live Test Cricket
programme.sub-title: South Africa v Pakistan: Second Test Day Five
programme.desc: South Africa v Pakistan. Coverage of the fifth and final day of the second test in the three-match series from Newlands Cricket Ground in Cape Town. This is the fourth time these nations have faced each other here in this format of the game, and coming into this contest the Proteas have a 100 per cent record. The most recent encounter took place in February 2013, and on that occasion the hosts claimed a four-wicket victory that was largely thanks to the second innings performance of their bowlers. Having dismissed Pakistan for 169 that set a winning target of 181, and despite a shaky start saw the hosts lose the opening wicket with just 10 runs on the board, the total proved to be achievable.

This is the fourth time these nations have faced each other here in this format of the game, and coming into this contest the Proteas have a 100 per cent record. The most recent encounter took place in February 2013, and on that occasion the hosts claimed a four-wicket victory that was largely thanks to the second innings performance of their bowlers. programme.title: NFL - Greatest Games
programme.desc: Miami Dolphins v San Diego Chargers. A review of the AFC Championship Game played in 1982, which came to be known as the `epic in Miami'. The Chargers started the first quarter in scintillating form, and raced to a 24-0 lead that appeared to have settled the contest in their favour early on. However, The Dolphins battled back in the second quarter, scoring 17 unanswered points to narrow the margin, and at the end of the fourth quarter the teams were tied at 38-38. Despite the extreme heat and humidity, and with many players suffering the effects of dehydration, it took a further 14 minutes of overtime before San Diego kicked a winning field goal to eventually claim a 41-28 victory, and progress to the Super Bowl.(n)
